pf.graph
Interface Vertex

All Superinterfaces:
Graph, java.lang.Iterable<Edge>
All Known Implementing Classes:
VertexImpl
public interface Vertex
extends Graph, java.lang.Iterable<Edge>

Graph provides a tree-like structure: it contains other Graph s and leaves are Vertexes. This is the reason why Vertex is a Graph.

Vertex provides all methods for edge management. Vertex has a location specified in integer x and y. It doesn't use Point from analytics package and it rather has its own implementation.

There often is a parameter used in some methods. It has a meaning of a restriction on usage of edges.

  • true - only unused edges
  • false - all edges

Author:
Adam Juraszek
